cards.card_body:
## What ID structure should I adopt?

So far I've been using a datetime string as an ID. I made this choice way back when I knew even less than I do now, and I'm coming across all sorts of issues because of that decision.

For one thing I'd converted the string into an INT, and the number itself is far too big for INTs. It should've stayed as a string. If it stays as a string then there's no reason to use a datetime string, it can be any random series of letters, which would make it shorter and have more combinations.
